436
00:34:03,060 --> 00:34:03,900
Four sheets.

437
00:34:04,230 --> 00:34:05,070
- Is that okay?
- Good. Good.

438
00:34:05,950 --> 00:34:06,860
Where should we put them?

439
00:34:08,060 --> 00:34:09,670
Here, they need to lie flat.

440
00:34:09,790 --> 00:34:10,630
Okay.

441
00:34:10,870 --> 00:34:11,830
That's it then.

442
00:34:11,830 --> 00:34:13,580
Come on, let's spread this out.

443
00:34:16,310 --> 00:34:17,150
Yes.

444
00:34:18,180 --> 00:34:20,310
Why did you buy these?

445
00:34:20,620 --> 00:34:22,260
Shanghai has all of these.

446
00:34:22,260 --> 00:34:23,740
Just give her more money.

447
00:34:23,950 --> 00:34:26,580
Your daughter's learned to be frugal.

448
00:34:26,580 --> 00:34:28,950
If you give her money,
she won't spend it.

449
00:34:30,830 --> 00:34:33,830
Do you think
starting a company is reliable?

450
00:34:34,220 --> 00:34:35,510
How do they calculate seniority?

451
00:34:36,350 --> 00:34:37,740
They're different from us.

452
00:34:38,060 --> 00:34:39,990
We've been in this one job
for our whole lives.

453
00:34:40,580 --> 00:34:42,660
Now, they don't even count seniority.

454
00:34:42,950 --> 00:34:44,870
They value development and prospects.

455
00:34:45,470 --> 00:34:46,660
If they catch a good opportunity,

456
00:34:46,910 --> 00:34:49,950
